## Component Customization

### ‚úÖ The ONLY Way to Customize UI

shadcn/ui components are copied into your codebase, which means you can customize them **WITHOUT creating new custom UI components**:

#### Allowed Customization Methods:

1. **Modify existing shadcn/ui components** in `components/ui/`
   ```tsx
   // Modify components/ui/button.tsx directly
   // Add new variants, change default styles, etc.
   ```

2. **Add new variants** using `class-variance-authority`
   ```tsx
   // In components/ui/button.tsx
   const buttonVariants = cva(
     "base-classes",
     {
       variants: {
         variant: {
           default: "...",
           destructive: "...",
           outline: "...",
           // ‚úÖ Add your custom variant here
           brand: "bg-brand text-white hover:bg-brand/90",
         },
       },
     }
   )
   ```

3. **Extend component props** as needed
   ```tsx
   // In components/ui/button.tsx
   export interface ButtonProps
     extends React.ButtonHTMLAttributes<HTMLButtonElement>,
       VariantProps<typeof buttonVariants> {
     // ‚úÖ Add custom props here
     isLoading?: boolean
   }
   ```

4. **Compose shadcn/ui components** into business logic components
   ```tsx
   // ‚úÖ CORRECT: Composing shadcn/ui components
   import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
   import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from "@/components/ui/card"
   
   export function StatusCard({ status, onUpdate }) {
     return (
       <Card>
         <CardHeader>
           <CardTitle>{status}</CardTitle>
         </CardHeader>
         <CardContent>
           <Button onClick={onUpdate}>Update Status</Button>
         </CardContent>
       </Card>
     )
   }
   ```

#### ‚ùå NOT Allowed:

- Creating new UI primitives from scratch (e.g., `components/custom-button.tsx`)
- Building UI components using only Tailwind without shadcn/ui
- Duplicating shadcn/ui functionality with custom implementations
- Using other UI libraries alongside shadcn/ui

